<subSubSection id="C31265272028FF8FFB01CCFEF82229E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="186" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB736AC2028FF8FFB01CCFEF78F2E59" blockId="0.[1257,2136,687,877]" pageId="0" pageNumber="186">• Very large, rotund baleen whales with girths and heads sometimes more than 60% and about 33% oftotal body length, respectively, broad, smooth backs with no dorsal fins or ridges, and large flukes and paddle-like flippers.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7766242028FF8FFB01CD1DFA2D2E72" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6595813" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6595813" box="[1257,1518,844,877]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6595813/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="186" startId="0.[1257,1270,844,877]" targetBox="[1454,1951,891,1080]" targetPageId="0">
